item.description:
A very simple yet useful command. Echos your input and automatically prompts you to print the page.
EXAMPLE print 222 Alexander Road; Somewhere, Somestate. (prints the given address)
--Jacob Ensor jacobensor.com {url[no url encoding] echo <html><head></head><body onload="javascript:window.print()">%s</body></html>}

Converts a string from one character set to another, similar to the iconv commmand/function in Unix and PHP.

Example: iconv -from UTF-8 -to UTF-16 -str test

The "from" and "to" parameters both default to UTF-8.

//IGNORE and //TRANSLIT are supported; see http://us3.php.net/manual/en/function.iconv.php for more information.

http://www.ibiblio.org/weidai/iconv_list.php lists known coded character sets. http://www.ibiblio.org/weidai/iconv.php?from=${from=UTF-8}&to=${to=UTF-8}&str=${str}

